---
title: "Memory Palace — Claim Lifecycle State Machine"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Extracted: LLM reads raw source

    state "Extracted" as Extracted {
        direction LR
        [*] --> Parsing: Source text → LLM
        Parsing --> Structured: entity + predicate + value
    }

    Extracted --> DeduplicateCheck: Entity alias resolution

    state "Deduplicate Check" as DeduplicateCheck {
        direction TB
        [*] --> ExistingEntity: Entity already known?
        ExistingEntity --> MergeAliases: Yes — merge aliases
        ExistingEntity --> CreateEntity: No — new entity
    }

    DeduplicateCheck --> ContradictionCheck: Claim vs existing claims

    state "Contradiction Check" as ContradictionCheck {
        direction TB
        [*] --> Compare: Same entity + predicate?
        Compare --> NoConflict: Values agree
        Compare --> Conflict: Values disagree
        Conflict --> LogContradiction: Write to contradiction table
        LogContradiction --> TemporalOrder: Which is newer?
        TemporalOrder --> SupersedeOld: New claim wins → old.superseded_by = new.id
        TemporalOrder --> MarkContested: Ambiguous → both marked "contested"
    }

    ContradictionCheck --> Active: Claim stored

    state "Active" as Active {
        direction TB
        state epistemic <<choice>>
        [*] --> epistemic
        epistemic --> Confirmed: High confidence + multiple sources
        epistemic --> Provisional: Single source, moderate confidence
        epistemic --> Contested: Contradicted, unresolved
    }

    Active --> Superseded: Newer claim replaces this one
    Active --> Retracted: Source discredited or manually flagged
    Active --> Expired: TTL elapsed (tactical claims only)
    Active --> Active: Updated (confidence change, new corroboration)

    Superseded --> [*]: Kept for audit trail\n(superseded_by points to replacement)
    Retracted --> [*]: epistemic_tag = "retracted"
    Expired --> [*]: Pruned by maintenance cron

    state "Cache Impact" as CacheImpact {
        direction TB
        [*] --> InvalidateL1: L1 cluster cache stale
        InvalidateL1 --> RegenerateL0: If claim touches L0 entities
        RegenerateL0 --> Done: Caches rebuilt
    }

    Active --> CacheImpact: Any state change invalidates caches

    note right of Active
        Active claims are the ONLY claims
        included in projection context.
        Superseded/Retracted/Expired claims
        are invisible to the LLM at query time
        but preserved for provenance audit.
    end note

    note right of ContradictionCheck
        Contradictions are first-class objects,
        not error states. They surface in lint
        reports and can be explicitly resolved
        by the human or by new evidence.
    end note
